  "prompt": "Who was the Guru of Guru Nanak Dev Ji?",
  "response": "The Guru of Guru Nanak Dev Ji was Guru Ram Das Ji. Guru Nanak, the founder of Sikhism, is considered the first Guru, while Guru Ram Das Ji is the fourth Guru in the line of Sikh Gurus. However, Guru Nanak did not have a human guru; he experienced divine revelation and enlightenment directly from God. In Sikhism, the lineage of Gurus is sacred, and Guru Nanak established the tradition of passing wisdom and spiritual authority through a line of Gurus.",
